{
  "texts": [
    "However, these works primarily focus on using rubrics to generate preference data or guide model behavior indirectly, whereas our approach directly incorporates rubric-based rewards into the reinforcement learning process to provide a more structured and interpretable feedback signal for instruction following.",
    "Concurrently, Gunjal et al. (2025) and Huang et al. (2025) also explore using rubric-based rewards for RL training, but they mainly focus on the synthetic rubric generation setting with relatively small-scale LLMs on general tasks.",
    "In contrast, our work focuses on the full-stack rubric-based training and evaluation pipeline to improve LLMs' instruction-following capabilities at scale, including high-quality human-annotated rubrics collection, rubric generator and verifier training, and large-scale RLHF training with rubric-based rewards.",
    "Our experiments on LLMs of varying scales demonstrate the effectiveness of our approach in enhancing instruction-following performance, particularly on complex tasks that require nuanced understanding and execution of instructions.",
    "Many real-world user instructions are inherently open-ended and cannot be easily assessed through automated scripts or simply prompted LLM judges without guidance, see Figure 1 for an example."
  ]
}